        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Update install telemetry and ranking signals",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move CLI install telemetry to one best-effort `install` event from `clawhub install`, while keeping legacy sync telemetry payloads accepted server-side.\n- Keep `clawhub sync` as a publishing/catalog command, but remove its install telemetry reporting.\n- Remove installs from recommended/search ranking signals so downloads and stars drive popularity ranking.\n- Add a temporal abuse signal for installs that track downloads too closely, with 7-day and 30-day evidence.\n- Calibrate the close-ratio signal from production data since Patrick's OpenClaw install telemetry PR merged: require high volume, a clearly high raw install/download ratio, and a binomial z-style excess score against the observed baseline.\n- Tune the close-ratio case toward obvious abuse: 1,000 downloads in 7d or 2,000 in 30d, at least 500 installs, install/download ratio >= 50%, and excess z-score >= 50.\n- Update CLI/docs/schema tests and documentation for the new telemetry model.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bunx convex codegen`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/lib/publisherAbuseScoring.test.ts --testNamePattern \"high-volume installs|statistically elevated|30-day close-ratio|observed high-end\"`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/lib/publisherAbuseScoring.test.ts convex/publisherAbuse.test.ts`\n- `env -u ARTIFACTORY_USERNAME -u ARTIFACTORY_PASSWORD NPM_CONFIG_REGISTRY=https://registry.npmjs.org BUN_CONFIG_REGISTRY=https://registry.npmjs.org bun run ci:static`\n- `bun run ci:unit`\n- `bun run ci:types-build`\n- Earlier on this PR: `bun run ci:packages`\n- Earlier on this PR: `AUTOREVIEW_AUTO_TESTS=0 .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` reported no actionable defects in its final text verdict. The wrapper still exited nonzero because it misclassified the clean summary line.\n\nNote: `ci:static` was run with npmjs registry env overrides because this machine has Artifactory registry environment variables that make `bun audit` return HTTP 400.\n",
